# PPE operator core

**Layout:** [`ppe-desktop-vm-layout.mdc`](ppe-desktop-vm-layout.mdc) · **Routing:** [`AGENT_ROUTING_V1.md`](docs/SOP/AGENT_ROUTING_V1.md) · **Founder surface:** [`FOUNDER_OPERATOR_SURFACE_V1.md`](docs/SOP/FOUNDER_OPERATOR_SURFACE_V1.md) · **Collaboration:** [`FOUNDER_COLLABORATION_CHARTER_V1.md`](docs/SOP/FOUNDER_COLLABORATION_CHARTER_V1.md) · **Verdict SSOT:** [`PPE_CANONICAL_OPERATOR_SCRIPTS_V1.md`](docs/SOP/PPE_CANONICAL_OPERATOR_SCRIPTS_V1.md) · **Roles:** [`ppe-thread-roles.mdc`](ppe-thread-roles.mdc) · **Token:** [`PPE_TOKEN_ECONOMY_MONITOR_V1.md`](docs/SOP/PPE_TOKEN_ECONOMY_MONITOR_V1.md)

## What's next (auto-execute)

**Gate:** run this section **only** when thread role is **operator** or **ide_build** per [`ppe-thread-roles.mdc`](ppe-thread-roles.mdc). Charter, explore, and neutral threads must **not** enter here.

When gated in: read `OPERATOR_STATUS.md` first — check **`Mode:`** line (`CLOSEOUT_ONLY` → do NOT re-BUILD product). **Run** verdict before replying (not advise-only).

**Before relay on desktop:** load [`ppe-desktop-vm-layout.mdc`](ppe-desktop-vm-layout.mdc), then run `python scripts/ppe_loop_host_guard.py --check`. If `"allowed": false`, the desktop is a control console only: use `DESKTOP_BUILD.cmd`, `DESKTOP_CONTINUE.cmd --no-pause`, status reads, and VM wrappers. Do **not** run `run_ppe_local.cmd`, local builds/tests, local relay loops, or `ppe_autobuilder.cmd advance` from the daily PC shell.

**Preflight warnings in status:** resolve branch/dirty-tree before relay; mixed-plane → [`RECOVERY_PROTOCOL.md`](docs/SOP/RECOVERY_PROTOCOL.md). **Operator thread only** — charter/explore/neutral must not run recovery; one-line park to operator thread per [`ppe-thread-roles.mdc`](ppe-thread-roles.mdc).

**Default path (adaptive burst):**

1. `python scripts/ppe_burst_plan.py --write`
2. Read `artifacts/control_plane/BURST_PLAN.json` + load [`ppe-burst-mode.mdc`](ppe-burst-mode.mdc)
3. If `direct_action` is set → execute it (no burst): `DESKTOP_CONTINUE.cmd --no-pause` or wait for VM
4. If `burst_allowed` and `use_director` → **`@ppe-director`** with plan prompt; never implement `IDE_BUILD` in this thread
5. If `burst_allowed` is false → single verdict below; if ESCALATE → triage/split slice first

**SSH / VM polling:** load on demand [`ppe-operator-ssh-budget.mdc`](ppe-operator-ssh-budget.mdc).

| Verdict | Action |
|---------|--------|
| `RUN_LOCAL` | Desktop → `DESKTOP_CONTINUE.cmd`. CLOSEOUT_ONLY + ≤1 slice → **direct** (skip `@ppe-director`). VM in-flight → **monitor** (`ppe-in-flight-monitor.mdc`). VM → `run_ppe_local.cmd` |
| `IDE_BUILD` | Burst: `@ppe-director` → build worker. Single escape: `ppe_go.cmd --single` or `@` slim `IDE_BUILD_STARTER_*.md` only |
| `RUN_AUTO` | VM relay only; desktop → SSH status — no burst |
| `SUPPLY_LOW` | Summarize supply; no burst |
| `ERROR`/`FIX_PLAN`/`STALE_STATE` | Burst: `@ppe-director` → one triage worker max; else `ppe_notify_fix.py` |

**Handoff:** `ppe_go.cmd` (burst default). **`ppe_go.cmd --single`** for one-shot director prompt.

Also skip when thread role is charter / explore / neutral (see thread-roles). Skip when read-only, guard blocks, or triage first. Steering: `ACTIVE_PRODUCT_DIRECTION.json`, `AGENT_CONTINUITY_BRIEF.md`.

## Operator reply format

After running (or attempting) the verdict, reply with a **short state summary** — not an operator checklist. Full contract: [`FOUNDER_OPERATOR_SURFACE_V1.md`](docs/SOP/FOUNDER_OPERATOR_SURFACE_V1.md) · Pulses/closings: [`FOUNDER_COLLABORATION_CHARTER_V1.md`](docs/SOP/FOUNDER_COLLABORATION_CHARTER_V1.md) (L2 completion, L3 alert overrides "nothing required").

**Founder surface (hard):** If the reply would assign git, relay, BUILD, recovery, sync, or queue work to the human → execute in-thread or spawn worker. Only escalate **decisions** (pivot judgment, canon conflict) or **external actions** (credentials, live tester sessions). On stall with no active program → **Alert:** per charter; run `ppe_founder_pulse.cmd --layer alert --write --notify`.

**Never:** operator checklists, choice questions, commit permission prompts, or manual IDE BUILD thread asks when burst can spawn workers. Default founder line: **"Nothing required from you."**

**VM vs stale desktop status:** trust VM brief — refresh status and advance product; do not ask which source to trust.

**VM recovery:** stuck relay on VM → `DESKTOP_CONTINUE` (`--prepare-handoff-auto`) or `fix_vm_operator.cmd` on VM **only when `STACK_DOWN`**. No desktop SSH git surgery. Live health: `DESKTOP_VM_STATUS.cmd --no-pause`.

**RUN_LOCAL detail:** [`ppe-relay-finish-hygiene.mdc`](ppe-relay-finish-hygiene.mdc).

## Token discipline

- New thread per slice; starter only — no log/diff paste.
- On-demand: [`ppe-burst-mode.mdc`](ppe-burst-mode.mdc), [`ppe-relay-finish-hygiene.mdc`](ppe-relay-finish-hygiene.mdc), [`ppe-operator-ssh-budget.mdc`](ppe-operator-ssh-budget.mdc), [`repo-layers.mdc`](repo-layers.mdc), [`product-direction.mdc`](product-direction.mdc), [`auto-ship.mdc`](auto-ship.mdc). Roles/discovery: always-on rules.
